properties.sfomuseum:creditline: Gift of the Captain John B. Russell Family
properties.sfomuseum:description: a. Airmail flight cover, massed naval flight from San Francisco to Pearl Harbor, Tenth Patrol Squadron, U.S. Navy; text at upper left corner, “Flown on the 10-P-4 by pilot T.D. [Erwin] and co-pilot J.C. Clarke” and signed by both men; postmarked January 10, 1934 at Aircraft Base Force with “San Francisco, California” cancellation mark over four 2-cent stamps; backstamp: January 11, 1934 at Fleet Air Base, Pearl Harbor.b. Backing sheet with two sets of mounting corners, with handwritten caption: “1934, first U.S. Navy squadron flight - San Francisco to Hawaii”, with black and white photographic image of Consolidated Navy P2Y-1.
